Eaton delves into the life of the Byrds founding member and his influence on the folk-rock scene and sheds light on Crosby's darker side as both a criminal and drug addict. As Crosby nears the end of his life, he continues to produce albums with the conviction that he still has much to contribute to the world of music.

Jones, Kathleen Wilhoite, David Lindstedt, Mark Kiely, Gordon Tootoosis.

John C. McGinley, Edward Asner, Adam Sandler.

Kristen Stewart, Forest Whitaker, Dwight Yoakam, Jared Leto.

What turns out to be an initially quick trip becomes an extended stay as father and son try to repair the house, and in the process find their own way of trying to repair their strained relationship.
